    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InLocoMediaUnavailableException, NetworkUnavailableException

    public class InLocoMediaAPIException
extends com.inlocomedia.android.resources.exception.InLocoMediaException
    Exception wrapping the exceptions for the API. It decodes the results and throw an appropriate error. Generally is one of the following errors: InLocoMediaUnavailableException, NetworkUnavailableException
    Can also throw RetailMapImageInvalidException, RetailMapsUnavailableException, InvalidFloorException, when dealing with maps.
    If any other error occurs, it will be explained in the Throwable.getMessage() method. Example: Wrong retail id utilized on a retail request. It won't throw a custom error, just a InLocoMediaAPIException with a message notifying the error.
